00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:55.000
Quick definition for people who are new to programming or outside of the consulting world.

00:50:55.000 --> 00:50:57.000
Agency work, what is that?

00:50:57.000 --> 00:51:10.000
So this would be like a development agency that builds some sort of thing -- could be a mobile app, could be a website, whatever it happens to be -- for a variety of different clients.

00:51:10.000 --> 00:51:14.000
So they have a range of clients they work with, and they get contracted, and you are a developer on that team.

00:51:14.000 --> 00:51:26.000
And I contrast that against being an in-house developer where you're like, "I work at IBM, and I manage all of the web properties for IBM," or "I build this app for IBM," whatever it happens to be.

00:51:26.000 --> 00:51:31.000
Yeah, "I build the authentication integration between all our internal apps and keep them running," or whatever.

00:51:31.000 --> 00:51:32.000
Yeah, exactly.

00:51:32.000 --> 00:51:36.000
So this is more like -- you're like a bee floating from client to client.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:39.000
Now, that can be awesome.

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:52.000
If you're the right kind of agency, that means you're constantly getting variety in clients and work, so you've got novelty, and you can just absolutely crush it with that kind of work.

00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:57.000
However, sometimes you have agencies that are like, "We build WordPress sites for ice cream shops.

00:51:57.000 --> 00:51:58.000
That's all we do.

00:51:58.000 --> 00:52:00.000
We know it."

00:52:00.000 --> 00:52:09.000
And you get to a point where it's cookie cutter, and that is just mind-numbingly boring.

00:52:09.000 --> 00:52:11.000
It can be easy work.

00:52:11.000 --> 00:52:19.000
It can be work that you do very effectively, that you can apply unique aspects of that to each of your different clients in different ways.

00:52:19.000 --> 00:52:24.000
But it can also run the danger of triggering the whole, "Oh, this is really boring.

00:52:24.000 --> 00:52:27.000
I can't get anything done" reflex.

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:36.000
And agencies often -- I'd say 90% of the time -- are really focused on billable hours.

00:52:36.000 --> 00:52:44.000
So a lot of what you're doing is saying, "I think it's going to take me X amount of hours to do," and then tracking how many hours it took you to do and billing those hours.

00:52:44.000 --> 00:52:48.000
And those two things are absolute nightmares for the ADHD brain.

00:52:48.000 --> 00:52:55.000
So if you find an agency that does flat billing where they're like, "We charge X to build you Y," awesome.

00:52:55.000 --> 00:53:00.000
Or they do a variety of different work, can be really awesome.

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:04.000
But often that's not the case.

00:53:04.000 --> 00:53:17.000
